anyway the bottom line is i'm currently at the "letting terrible things happen while the wizard yells at you and fears you didn't even know you had consume your every waking thought cause you calmed the old ones down" phase and I just wish it would end
@timescanner no joints only bone

it's a terrible disease that actively tries to destroy everything that matters to you under the guise of "protecting" you. and I don't know if it ever goes away. i despair at the thought of playing this whack-a-mole game for the rest of my life.

but eventually you see the wizard is lying to you! and just thinking about a terrible thing WON'T make it happen!

at least for that topic anyway! but guess what! once one OCD theme goes down, another, more horrible one pops up in its place! it's an eternal infernal whack-a-mole!

then you find out that the only way to break the wizard's curse is to actively let the things you are most scared of happening just HAPPEN. meanwhile the wizard is shouting in your ear "IF YOU EVEN THINK ABOUT YOUR LOVED ONES DYING THEY WILL DIE. THIS IS AN IMMUTABLE LAW"

and sometimes your actions (which are meant to save your loved ones!) actually end up hurting them instead, or they don't understand and get annoyed, and it hurts cause like all i was trying to do was save you, and now i hurt you instead

meanwhile your friends and family don't know about the wizard and don't understand that you're saving them by trying to stop the things from happening. all they see is the distressing & bizarre actions that seem disconnected from reality, and only YOU know the truth

and then you start taking action to make sure the things you keep thinking about won't happen, except that makes you think about them more, which leads you to take increasingly bizarre and distressing actions to stop the thing

you wanna know what OCD is like? it's like a wizard appears to you and says "everything you think about will come true" except then you can only think about the things you're MOST scared of in the world

This post sponsored by: deleting all my social media apps so all I have left is scrolling through LinkedIn.

/FIN, exit stage right

Everything right now is fine. My current job is great and sometimes I even feel that spark of passion & ambition again. I just……I have wanted to talk about this for so long. I hope you will be gentle with me.

It feels so stupid that this still affects me. That every few months I still dream of the place. That ~this~ is the one thing my brain has decided to be most traumatized by. Not my dad almost dying, not the forest fire, not being robbed. ~This.~
I guess I didn’t want my old IDEO colleagues to find out what I felt about it.

I don’t know what I hope to gain by posting this. Some kind of release, I guess. I spent the year after I came back posting sad song lyrics on instagram and desperate veiled stories on my website. I guess I felt I wasn’t allowed to feel crushed by such an incredible opportunity.

So yeah, I feel kind of weird and jealous about seeing my old IDEO colleagues’ careers on LinkedIn.

I rarely talk about my IDEO stint at work. It’s like a secret & a byword, a strange part of my origin story wrapped in several kinds of shame.

Of course if all of that hadn’t happened I never would have met Laz, never would have become the Desert Prophet, never would have started the ARCH-HIVE, never would have met Rusden. It’s just weird to think about this other life I ~almost~ had.

I had been on a trajectory to have an international design career but instead I stayed in Provo and did art and worked at a bookstore and picked up the pieces. Eventually I found myself at a good UX job but that intense passion that would have propelled me to the stars was gone.
Obviously I was crushed and spent my last year of school in a hopeless miasma. All I could think about was Icarus. I had flown too close to the sun and drowned in dark water.

At the end I asked my boss for feedback to get an idea of whether they would hire me back when I graduated. He told me he caught on to everything I was “fake-it-till-you-make-it”-ing, that I did poorly at things I thought I did well, & insinuated I should find a different career.

When I was 21, I got an internship at the top design firm in the world. I loved it and it felt like coming home. All I wanted was to work there forever. But it was my first internship and I was in way over my head.
I haven’t talked about this publicly because I didn’t want it to negatively affect my career and yes my boss follows me on here but he already knows all this (hi bryan yes i am fine) so here goes

i’m mad about “influencers”. why do they have so many followers??? why??????

i’m grateful for the reach that social media has given me so far and all the connections I’ve made. but also i’m so so frustrated that dumb videos of people squishing slime get MILLIONS AND MILLIONS OF VIEWS

and yes, maybe I want influence because I have a dumb big ego and I think my ideas and creations are worth getting some attention. I may not do much but my mind is a swirling mass of connections & ideas. it’s a shame i’m so inconsistent at getting them out into the world.

for years now I have craved influence. because I have been so deeply touched by other works of art & music and I WANT my work to do the same for people. LOTS OF PEOPLE. so they can see things how I see. so if they’re like me, maybe they can feel a little less alone.
